text = "[b][font_size=21]How to use the SceneMap Plugin[/font_size][/b]
[b]Adding components to a scene[/b]
[ol]
 Create a new script that inherits from the [code]SceneMapComponent2D[/code] class.
 Add a node in the scene and attach that script to it.
[/ol]

[b]Adding scenes to the map[/b]
[ol]
 Use the [img=%20]res://addons/scene_map_plugin/assets/add-icon.svg[/img] or button drag a .tscn file to add a new scene to the map.
 Drag and drop the arrow slots [img=%18]res://addons/scene_map_plugin/assets/arrow-double.svg[/img] to connect one scene to another.
 Use the controls in each slot to disconnect them [img=%18]res://addons/scene_map_plugin/assets/disconnect-icon.svg[/img] or change their side [img=%18]res://addons/scene_map_plugin/assets/sides-icon.svg[/img], type [img=%18]res://addons/scene_map_plugin/assets/type-icon.svg[/img] or name [img=%18]res://addons/scene_map_plugin/assets/edit-icon.svg[/img]
 Press DEL while having one or more nodes selected to remove them from the map.
[/ol]

[b]Notes and recommendations[/b]
[ul]
It is recommended to close all scenes while working with this plugin.
